uniqueness
proof
given g1,g2 such that
A2: (for r holds (r > ( 0 ) implies (ex n st (for m holds (n <= m implies ( dist (( S1 . m ),g1) ) < r)))))
and
A3: (for r holds (r > ( 0 ) implies (ex n st (for m holds (n <= m implies ( dist (( S1 . m ),g2) ) < r)))))
and
A4: g1 <> g2;

set a = ( ( dist (g1,g2) ) / 4 );
A5: ( dist (g1,g2) ) >= ( 0 ) by METRIC_1:5;
A6: ( dist (g1,g2) ) <> ( 0 ) by A4,METRIC_1:2;
then consider n1 such that A7: (for m holds (n1 <= m implies ( dist (( S1 . m ),g1) ) < a)) by A2,A5,XREAL_1:224;
consider n2 such that A8: (for m holds (n2 <= m implies ( dist (( S1 . m ),g2) ) < a)) by A3,A6,A5,XREAL_1:224;
set k = ( n1 + n2 );
A9: ( dist (( S1 . k ),g2) ) < a by A8,NAT_1:12;
A10: ( dist (g1,g2) ) <= ( ( dist (g1,( S1 . k )) ) + ( dist (( S1 . k ),g2) ) ) by METRIC_1:4;
( dist (( S1 . k ),g1) ) < a by A7,NAT_1:12;
then ( ( dist (g1,( S1 . k )) ) + ( dist (( S1 . k ),g2) ) ) < ( a + a ) by A9,XREAL_1:8;
then ( dist (g1,g2) ) < ( ( dist (g1,g2) ) / 2 ) by A10,XXREAL_0:2;
hence contradiction by A6,A5,XREAL_1:216;
end;
